.TH "TILDR\-COMMANDS" "1" "2026" "Tildr" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tildr\-commands \[em] command reference for Tildr
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]tildr\f[R] \f[I]<command>\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
[\f[I]target\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This page documents all commands available in \f[B]tildr(1)\f[R].
.PP
The \f[B]add\f[R], \f[B]restore\f[R], and \f[B]unlink\f[R] commands
accept multiple file parameters simultaneously:
.IP
.EX
tildr add .config/nvim/init.vim .config/nvim/lua/plugins.lua
tildr restore .config/nvim/init.vim .config/nvim/lua/plugins.lua
.EE
.PP
If a path contains spaces, use single or double quotes:
.IP
.EX
tildr unlink \[aq].config/my app/config.toml\[aq] .config/nvim/init.vim
.EE
.SH COMMANDS
.SS tildr init
Initializes the Tildr repository and writes the user configuration
file.
.IP
.EX
tildr init
tildr init \-\-repo \[ti]/.dotfiles\-work
tildr init \-\-no\-git
tildr init \-\-force
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-r\f[R], \f[B]\[en]repo\f[R] \f[I]<PATH>\f[R]
Repository path, which must be inside \f[CR]$HOME\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]no\-git\f[R]
Skip \f[CR]git init\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-f\f[R], \f[B]\[en]force\f[R]
Reinitialize even if config already exists.
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]
Suppress output.
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates the repository directory
.IP \[bu] 2
Writes \f[CR]\[ti]/.config/tildr/config.toml\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Detects whether Git is available in \f[CR]PATH\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Writes \f[CR][git].available\f[R] to the config
.IP \[bu] 2
Initializes a Git repository only when Git is available and
\f[CR]\-\-no\-git\f[R] is not used
.IP \[bu] 2
Refuses \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] itself as the repository root
.IP \[bu] 2
Refuses repositories outside \f[CR]$HOME\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
If already initialized and \f[CR]\-\-force\f[R] is not passed, refreshes
the saved Git availability state
.SS tildr add
Adds a file or a directory tree from \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] into the
repository and replaces each file with a symlink.
.IP
.EX
tildr add .bashrc
tildr add .config/nvim
tildr add .config/nvim/init.lua \-\-dry\-run
tildr add .bashrc .config/nvim/init.lua
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]
Preview actions without modifying files.
.TP
\f[B]\-f\f[R], \f[B]\[en]force\f[R]
Remove an existing repository target before moving the file.
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]
Suppress output.
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Files are moved into the repository
.IP \[bu] 2
Symlinks are created at the original home path
.IP \[bu] 2
Directories are traversed recursively
.IP \[bu] 2
Paths matched by \f[CR].tildrignore\f[R] are skipped
.IP \[bu] 2
Already\-correct symlinks are skipped silently
.IP \[bu] 2
If \f[CR]git.auto_commit = true\f[R], the repository is auto\-committed
after a successful run
.SS tildr apply
Applies repository state into \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] by creating or repairing
symlinks.
.IP
.EX
tildr apply
tildr apply \-\-dry\-run
tildr apply \-\-force \-\-verbose
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]
Preview actions.
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\[en]verbose\f[R]
Include unchanged or skipped entries in output.
.TP
\f[B]\-f\f[R], \f[B]\[en]force\f[R]
Replace conflicting regular files or directories in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-q\f[R], \f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]
Suppress output.
.PP
\f[B]Behavior:\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates missing symlinks for all managed files
.IP \[bu] 2
Repairs broken or incorrect symlinks automatically
.IP \[bu] 2
Skips regular files already present in \f[CR]$HOME\f[R] unless
\f[CR]\-\-force\f[R] is used
.IP \[bu] 2
Uses the repository as the source of truth
.IP \[bu] 2
Does not modify repository content
.SS tildr status
Shows the synchronization state of all managed files.
.IP
.EX
tildr status
tildr status \-\-json
tildr status \-\-counter
.EE
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]\-j\f[R], \f[B]\[en]json\f[R]
Emit structured JSON output.
.TP
\f[B]\-c\f[R], \f[B]\[en]counter\f[R]
Print aggregated counters only.
.PP
\f[B]Status values:\f[R]
.TP
\f[CR]linked\f[R]
Symlink exists and points to the correct repository file.
.TP
\f[CR]missing_link\f[R]
Repository file exists but the home symlink is absent.
.TP
\f[CR]broken_symlink\f[R]
A symlink exists but points to a wrong target.
.TP
\f[CR]not_a_symlink\f[R]
A regular file or directory exists where the symlink should be.
.PP
The \f[B]\[en]counter\f[R] mode prints a summary:
.IP
.EX
Managed: 12
Linked: 10
Missing: 1
Broken: 0
Not symlink: 1
.EE
.SS tildr list
